e (we can run it in the foreground, without backgrounding, because we are in a cron job and need the output).\n 3. The tool will return the output, which we then return as the summary.\n\n However, note: the cron job expects the summary to be returned as plain text. So we must capture the stdout of the script.\n\n We'll set `background: false` (default) so we wait for the command to finish and get the output.\n\n Let's call the tool.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me run the stock monitor script to get the latest updates:\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_614367436895467dac155d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 /workspace/skills/stock-monitor/scripts/stocks_monitor.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-dashscope-aliyuncs-com","model":"deepseek-r1","usage":{"input":12269,"output":1174,"cacheRead":2494,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15937,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772699880091}}
