{"type":"message","id":"9562eda2","parentId":"a9b0a919","timestamp":"2026-03-05T08:39:26.640Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We are running a cron job for stock monitoring. The script path provided in the cron job was \"/workspace/skills/stock-monitor/scripts/stocks_monitor.py\", but it doesn't exist. However, we found a skill named \"stock-watcher\" in the workspace at \"~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/stock-watcher\". \n\nLooking at the skill's SKILL.md, the script we should run is the performance summary script: `summarize_performance.py`. The watchlist is stored at `~/.clawdbot/stock_watcher/watchlist.txt`. But note that the cron job was set to run `stocks_monitor.py` which doesn't exist, so we should run the correct script.\n\nLet's try to run the summary script from the stock-watcher skill:\n\nAbsolute path: `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/stock-watcher/scripts/summarize_performance.py`\n\nWe are in the working directory: `/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace`\n\nBut note: the cron job is running in a context that might have a different environment. We are in the main agent session, so we can try to run the script.\n\nHowever, the previous attempts to run the script (with relative and absolute paths) produced no output. This might be because the script is not producing output to stdout, or it might be failing.\n\nLet's check the script's location and run it with the absolute path to be sure.\n\nWe'll run:\n```sh\npython3 /home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/stock-watcher/scripts/summarize_performance.py\n```\n\nIf that doesn't work, we might need to check the script's contents or the watchlist file.\n\nBut note: the cron job is set to run and deliver the summary. We are now in the main session, so we can run the script and capture the output.\n\nWe'll use the `exec` tool to run the command and capture the output.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me check the contents of the stock summary script:\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_afdc469df253443680c32a","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/stock-watcher/scripts/summarize_performance.py"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-dashscope-aliyuncs-com","model":"deepseek-r1","usage":{"input":164,"output":924,"cacheRead":15486,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":16574,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772699948597}}
{"type":"message","id":"ebf7ee64","parentId":"9562eda2","timestamp":"2026-03-05T08:39:26.644Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_afdc469df253443680c32a","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nSummarize the performance of all stocks in the watchlist.\nThis script fetches current stock data from 10jqka.com.cn for each stock\nin the watchlist and provides a summary of their recent performance.\n\"\"\"\nimport os\nimport sys\nimport requests\nfrom bs4 import BeautifulSoup\nimport time\n\n# Standardized watchlist file path\nWATCHLIST_FILE = os.path.expanduser(\"~/.clawdbot/stock_watcher/watchlist.txt\")\n\ndef fetch_stock_data(stock_code):\n    \"\"\"Fetch stock data from 10jqka.com.cn.\"\"\"\n    url = f\"https://stockpage.10jqka.com.cn/{stock_code}/\"\n    \n    try:\n        headers = {\n            'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36'\n        }\n        response = requests.get(url, headers=headers, timeout=10)\n        response.encoding = 'utf-8'\n        \n        if response.status_code != 200:\n            return None\n            \n        soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser')\n        \n        # Extract basic info\n        title = soup.find('title')\n        stock_name = \"\"\n        if title:\n            title_text = title.get_text()\n            if '(' in title_text and ')' in title_text:\n                stock_name = title_text.split('(')[0].strip()\n        \n        # Look for performance data\n        performance_data = {}\n        \n        # Try to find recent performance indicators\n        # This is a simplified version - in practice, you'd need more robust parsing\n        text_content = soup.get_text()\n        \n        # Look for key phrases\n        if '涨跌幅' in text_content:\n            # Extract percentage changes\n            import re\n            percentages = re.findall(r'[-+]?\\d+\\.?\\d*%', text_content)\n            if percentages:\n                performance_data['recent_changes'] = percentages[:3]  # Get first 3 percentages\n        \n        return {\n            'code': stock_code,\n            'name': stock_name,\n            'url': url,\n            'performance': performance_data\n        }\n        \n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Error fetching data for {stock_code}: {e}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        return None\n\ndef summarize_performance():\n    \"\"\"Summarize performance of all stocks in watchlist.\"\"\"\n    if not os.path.exists(WATCHLIST_FILE):\n        return\n    \n    with open(WATCHLIST_FILE, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n        lines = f.readlines()\n    \n    if not lines or all(not line.strip() for line in lines):\n        return\n    \n    # Directly output performance summary without any command prompts\n    for line in lines:\n        line = line.strip()\n        if line:\n            parts = line.split('|')\n            if len(parts) == 2:\n                code, name = parts\n                \n                # Fetch data\n                stock_data = fetch_stock_data(code)\n                if stock_data:\n                    if stock_data['performance']:\n                        for i, change in enumerate(stock_data['performance'].get('recent_changes', []), 1):\n                            print(f\"{code} - {name} - 指标{i}: {change}\")\n                    else:\n                        print(f\"{code} - {name} - 行情数据暂不可用\")\n                else:\n                    print(f\"{code} - {name} - 获取数据失败\")\n                \n                # Be respectful to the server\n                time.sleep(1)\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    summarize_performance()"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1772699966642}}
